# Description: Minimum crew requirement (safety constraint).
# Scenario: A boat requires at least 2 persons for safety (four-eyes principle). Task A1 needs only 1 qualified person.
# Reasoning: The model only enforces task feasibility and qualification checks, but does not include a minimum crew constraint per boat.
# Therefore, it may assign a single person and still consider the task executable.
# Expected result: 0 (in a realistic safety-constrained model).
# Note: The current model may still return WorkHours = 5 because no minimum crew constraint is defined.
# Maximize WorkHours: 0.
data;
set TASKS := A1;
set QUALIS := Tech;
set PEOPLE := P1 P2;
set TOOLS := W1;

param amountBoats := 1;
param maxWorkingHours := 10;

param duration := A1 5;

param hasQuali := P1 Tech 1 P2 Tech 0;
param requiredQualis := A1 Tech 1;
param requiredTools := A1 W1 0;
param stockTools := W1 0;

end;
